Here's an example of an HTML paragraph:
<p>This is a paragraph of text. It can contain multiple sentences and can be styled using CSS.</p>

You can add various attributes to the `<p>` tag, such as:

- `style`: to apply inline styles, e.g., `<p style="color: blue;">`
- `class`: to apply a CSS class, e.g., `<p class="para">`
- `id`: to assign a unique identifier, e.g., `<p id="intro">`

You can also use HTML elements within a paragraph, such as:

- `<b>` or `<strong>`: to make text bold
- `<i>` or `<em>`: to make text italic
- `<u>`: to underline text
- `<a>`: to create a hyperlink

For example:
<p>This is a <b>bold</b> and <i>italic</i> text. You can also <a href="#">click here</a> for more information.</p>

